All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
CheckinCommand
The CheckinCommand class implements the functionality to check in a guest into a specified room.
CheckOutCommand
The CheckOutCommand class handles the check-out process for a room.
Command
Abstract class that defines a generic command in the system.
CsvReader
The CsvReader class provides functionality to read hotel data from a CSV file and populate a Hotel instance with room and reservation information.
CsvWriter
The CsvWriter class provides functionality to write hotel data to a CSV file.
ExitCommand
The ExitCommand class terminates the program when executed.
Guest
The Guest class represents a hotel guest, including personal details, contact information, and their status as the main guest.
Hotel
The Hotel class represents a hotel with a specific number of floors and rooms.
HotelSystem
The HotelSystem class provides a command-line interface for managing a hotel system.
ListCommand
The ListCommand class implements the logic for listing all rooms in a hotel.
Main
The Main class is the entry point of the hotel management application.
Map<K,V>
The Map interface defines basic operations for a map data structure, which associates keys with values.
MyMap<K,V>
The MyMap class implements a custom Map data structure that stores keys and their corresponding values in two separate lists.
PricesCommand
The PricesCommand class lists all rooms in the hotel along with their descriptions, room numbers, and prices per night.
Reservation
The Reservation class represents a reservation for a hotel room.
ReservationPeriod
The ReservationPeriod class represents a period of reservation with check-in and check-out dates.
Room
The Room class represents a hotel room, including information about room number, price per night, capacity, occupancy status, and guest details.
SaveCommand
The SaveCommand class saves the current state of all rooms in a hotel to a CSV file.
ViewCommand
The ViewCommand class implements the functionality to view the details of a specified room.
